about.description:
This is a flake8 plugin for validating Python docstrings markup as reStructuredText
(RST) using the Python library docutils, called via Todd Wolfson's package
restructuredtext-lint.
about.summary: Extension for flake8 for validating Python docstrings as reStructuredText

name: flake8-rst-docstrings
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "flake8-rst-docstrings" %}
{% set version = "0.0.12" %}
{% set sha256 = "01d38327801781b26c3dfeb71ae37e5a02c5ca1b774a686f63feab8824ca6f9c" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - flake8 >=3
    - restructuredtext_lint

test:
  commands:
    - "flake8 --version | grep rst-docstrings:"

about:
  home: https://github.com/peterjc/flake8-rst-docstrings
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.rst
  summary: 'Extension for flake8 for validating Python docstrings as reStructuredText'
  dev_url: https://github.com/peterjc/flake8-rst-docstrings
  description: |
    This is a flake8 plugin for validating Python docstrings markup as reStructuredText
    (RST) using the Python library docutils, called via Todd Wolfson's package
    restructuredtext-lint.

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - peterjc
